Package fr.ens.biologie.generic

package fr.ens.biologie.generic
Defines interfaces for basic operations that are used all the time and everywhere in big applications. This is really the core of this library.
Author:
Jacques Gignoux - 18 mai 2021
  • Interface Summary
    Interface
    Description
    DataContainer
    An interface for objects that contain data.
    Factory<T>
    An interface for factories for objects of class T.
    Initialisable
    An interface for objects that require initialisation (whatever this means) after instantiation.
    JavaCode
    An interface for classes which return a java source code as text, typically code generators.
    JavaGenerator
    An interface for classes generating java code.
    LimitedEdition<T>
    An interface that returns a limited set of instances, associated to unique ids.
    Resettable
    An interface for objects that can be reset to an initial state after having been brought into a different state.
    SaveableAsText
    An interface for objects that can be saved as text (in text files or Strings) and later re-loaded with a (static) valueOf() method.
    Sealable
    This interface is for objects that can be modified for a certain time, and then be sealed so that no future change is permitted.
    Showable
    An interface for things that can display themselves graphically in a separate window (for debugging, mainly).
    Singleton<T>
    An interface for a singleton instance of class T.
    Sizeable
    An interface for objects which have a size.
    Textable
    An interface for relatively complex objects that can return information with various levels of detail.
    Versionable
    An interface to put version numbers on objects.
    WriteProtectable
    An interface for objects that can be write protected / write enabled.
